read clayton christensen 's books instead this book covers much of the same ground that clayton christensen explored in his three revolutionary books : the innovator 's dilemma , the innovator 's solution , and seeing what 's next . truthfully , those books do a far superior job of explaining the dynamics of innovation in comparison to the performance of this book . utterback does have very insightful comments on the standardization of product design , but outside of that section , the book is not particularly exemplary . for those interested in mastering the art of innovation , the game begins and ends with clayton christensen